bug.short_desc: [compare] compare dialog lines between text disappear in high contrast mode.

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86539 normal appearance
Build ID: I20070621-1340
Steps To Reproduce: 1. create 2 text files 2. select both in navigator and do compare with "each other" 3. you should see some black lines between areas of the text file which have differences. 4. set the display to use high contrast via Control Panel -> Accessibility Options -> Display -> "Use High Contrast". 5. close the workbench and do the compare again. 6. The lines connecting the text areas are still black and can not be seen in high contrast mode.
More information: Shouldn't be hard to reproduce. See the attached images. This was discovered on Eclipse 3.2.2 but also happens in 3.3.0. Not sure about 3.4. In high contrast I would expect the lines to be white. Or at least be visible.

Affirmative, the "Compare with each other" is missing the lines while in the High Contrast mode. I've checked it on I20080108-1320. Kurtis how do you find colors used in the compare editor when comparing with a remote revision? Do you think they should be replaced with white too?
Created attachment 86558 Preference used to change compare line colors
Created attachment 86559 Compare dialog in high contrast with preference changed.

I found a preference to control the color of the compare decorations. It's under Windows->Preferences->General->Appearance->Colors and Fonts->Text Compare->"Outgoing Change Color" (see attached image). As far as I'm concerned this is an INVALID defect.
In reference to Tomasz Zarna comment. I'm uncertain about colors used when comparing with a remote revision. I don't use that feature too often. I recommend you to try the preference I mentioned above. Also there is a "resolved change color" preference which may be related.
